      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RAPIDO KUNA (1) has been settling off the speed lately, finishing sixth (35.99) last time in a Grade 5 at this track. Has ability and looks hard to stop. AUSSIE BROOK (2) started big odds last time but hit the ground running with a strong early split, giving a sight but fading only late to finish third (27.73) at Mandurah over 488m. Likely to be in the finish again. KING NANGAR (6) has a strong record this track and trip with three wins and two placings from six starts. Was out of the placings last time (27.73) at Mandurah in a OPEN, finishing fourth and beaten 3.5 lengths. Can feature with the right run. HUDSON (8) finished in the placings last start and deserves some thought.",
